HEADWORD: chinaware
<hw>chinaware</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>dishes made of china; porcelain; -- so called in the 17th century
because brought from the far East, and differing from the pottery made
in Europe at that time; also, loosely, crockery in general.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

